headline: Humana Expands Virtual Care And AI Support As Shares Trade Lower
summary: Humana partnered with Carda Health to expand access to virtual cardiac and pulmonary rehabilitation for its members. The company introduced Agent Assist, an AI tool designed to support member advocates in call centers and improve service quality. These moves reflect Humana's focus on digital health services and support for older adults with chronic conditions. For investors following NYSE:HUM, these updates arrive as the stock trades at $193.94, with returns of a 29.9% decline over 30 days...

headline: Is It Time To Reassess Humana (HUM) After Its Sharp Multi‑Year Share Price Slide
summary: If you are wondering whether Humana's current share price really reflects what the business is worth, you are not alone. This article is designed to help you weigh that up calmly and clearly. Humana's shares last closed at US$193.94, with returns of a 0.6% decline over 7 days, a 29.9% decline over 30 days, a 26.7% decline year to date, a 28.3% decline over 1 year, a 59.8% decline over 3 years and a 46.7% decline over 5 years.
